gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 119, Mavericks 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Mavericks, 119-101. Naz Reid led Minnesota with 27 points (career-high seven 3PT FG) and six rebounds as Karl-Anthony Towns (21 points, 17 rebounds) and Anthony Edwards (nine points, 11 assists) totaled 30 points as Minnesota outscored Dallas 60-41 in the second half. Luka Doncic led Dallas with 39 points, 13 assists, and six rebounds. Minnesotas win snaps a 4-game win streak for Dallas as they improve to 18-5 while the Mavericks move to 15-9.
